35
00:02:10,420 --> 00:02:13,969
In practice, people are not always aware
of those two aspects.

36
00:02:13,969 --> 00:02:19,890
They may even call an open-bottom pit a septic
tank, which is actually wrong.

37
00:02:19,890 --> 00:02:25,279
Blackwater and greywater enter the tank through
an inlet T.

38
00:02:25,279 --> 00:02:29,900
Settleable solids fall down to the bottom,
where they accumulate as sludge.

39
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:35,950
With time, the sludge undergoes some stabilization
by anaerobic digestion.

40
00:02:35,950 --> 00:02:39,639
It has to be removed every 3-5 years.

41
00:02:39,639 --> 00:02:43,529
Floatable substances move up to the surface,
forming a scum layer.

42
00:02:43,529 --> 00:02:48,169
The effluent from the clearwater zone, in
the middle, flows out through an outlet T

43
00:02:48,169 --> 00:02:53,950
